<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5030502>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 9. Gracilentulus aokii Imadaté, holotype (NSMT-Ap 78). A) dorsal view of thoraces I–II, left side; B) dorsal view of abdominal segment V–VII, right side; C) ventral view of abdominal segments V–VII right side; D) pore psm on abdominal tergite VIII; E) dorsal view of telson. Abbreviations: al, anterolateral pore; lt, laterotergal pore; psm, posterosubmedial pore; psl, posterosublateral pore; sl, sublateral pore; spsm, sternal posterosubmedial pore. Arrows indicate pores. Scale bars: 20 μm for A–C; 10 μm for D–F." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/5030502/files/figure.png" .

